=E2=96=A1 35 x 21 mm</td> </tr> <tr> <td>Weight</td> <td>12g</td> </tr> </t=
body> </table> </section> <section id=3D"the-project"> <h2>The Project</h2>=
 <p>These modules are the result of a lot of hard work to make the best cam=
era technology on the market available for drones, mobile robots and any ot=
her project you might think of.</p> <p>Our campaign budget here is the smal=
lest viable production run we can do. Your support will help us gain the tr=
action we need to get these great camera modules in your hands.</p> <p>Righ=
t now we have 8 prototype cameras (the ones in the photos). The camera modu=
les themselves have already been tested by our production partner, the gree=
n carrier PCBs are in testing now. The prototypes are also used for driver =
development and debugging, which is a work-in-progress. We expect most feat=
ures working by the time we ship out the first batch of production modules.=
</p> <p>The production camera modules will be nearly identical to the shown=
 prototypes. The main change is the 'frame sync' function. The prototypes c=
an only output this signal, the production modules will be able to use this=
 as input as well, allowing hardware frame synchronization between multiple=
 modules.</p> </section> <section id=3D"platform-support"> <h2>Platform Sup=
port</h2> <p>Drivers are in development for Nvidia Jetson boards, Raspberry=
 Pi boards and our upcoming Machine Learning focused Rockchip RK3588 platfo=
rm. Updates and links to drivers will be posted here when ready.</p> </sect=
ion> <section id=3D"order-now"> <h2>Order now!</h2> <p>The first production=
 run is available for an introduction price at Indiegogo.</p> <p>Get your C=
50M now <a href=3D"https://igg.me/at/c50m">@Indiegogo</a> and spread the wo=
